# Intuition
We have to find a window string(needle) in a haystack string. So we create two pointers which are used to traverse through string checking for first appearance of string.

# Approach
For loop for traversing through haystack. Create two pointers (j and ptr). j gets intialized as beginning of needle. create a count.
Create a while loop with conditon that, char at both pointers is equal, and ptr is less than needle length(so that we don't corss above our window)
After while loop ends if count==needle length, then voila! we have found our needle in our haystack. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(m*n)


Please Upvote!
P.S:-Trying out posting solution for first time.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int strStr(string haystack, string needle) {
        for(int i=0;i<haystack.length();i++)
        {
            int j=i;
            int ptr=0;
            int count=0;
            while(haystack[j]==needle[ptr] && ptr<needle.length())
            {
                j++;
                ptr++;
                count++;
            }
            if(count==needle.length()) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
```

