**Note:** This is an updated version of a previous post I wrote, just changed some formatting.

---
Relatively straightforward problem, just brute-forcing works marvelously. 

In my taste, this should be an ```easy``` problem, but even if it is placed ```medium```, it is definitely in the easy portion of all the mediums on Leetcode.

Let's get in our problem.

We simply search for a possible substring with the first character of ```needle```. If it occurs, check if the other characters match with each other. If it works, return the ```index```. Or else, forget about it and continue.

If anything is **unclear**, feel free to **comment** below.

Here is the code for reference. The **second tab** contains **detailed explanations line-by-line.**

```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int strStr(string haystack, string needle) {
        if (needle.size() > haystack.size()) return -1;
        for (int i = 0; i <= haystack.size() - needle.size(); i++) {
            if (needle[0] == haystack[i]) {
                bool flag = true;
                for (int j = 1; j < needle.size(); j++) if (needle[j] != haystack[i + j]) flag = false;
                if (flag) return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
```
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int strStr(string haystack, string needle) {
        // if the needle size is bigger than the haystack's size, the needle would obviously be too big
        if (needle.size() > haystack.size()) return -1; 
        for (int i = 0; i <= haystack.size() - needle.size(); i++) {
            // if first chars match each other, or if it is a possible candidate
            if (needle[0] == haystack[i]) { 
                bool flag = true;
                // if any other letters don't match, forget about it (flag = false)
                for (int j = 1; j < needle.size(); j++) if (needle[j] != haystack[i + j]) flag = false;
                // if the whole needle matches, with the haystack substring, return da answer!
                if (flag) return i; 
            }
        }
        // else, simply return -1 because none can be found
        return -1;
    }
};
```

