# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
problem is on pattern searching algorithm

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Rabin Karp algorithm
For tutorial video: [Rabin Karp Algorithm](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-WdkLyTeZ3Q)
Concept of [String Hashing](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JEOj8U54Cek) used in tutorial

# Complexity
n = length of the needle 
h = length of the haystack
- Time complexity: O(n+h)


<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int strStr(string h, string n) {
        // here n =needle and h=haystack

        long long int q=31, m=1e9+7; 
        long long int P=n.length();
        long long int S=h.length();
        if(S<P) return -1;   // example: needle='aaaa' and haystack = "aaa"
        vector<long long int> power(S, 1);

        for(int i=1;i<S;i++)  //precomputation of powers with base q
        {
            power[i]=(power[i-1]*q)%m;
        }

        long long int hash_n=0;  
        for(int i=0;i<P;i++)  // precompute the hash value of needle
        {
            hash_n=(hash_n+((n[i]-'a'+1)*power[i])%m)%m;
        }
        vector<long long int> hash(S+1, 0);
        for(int i=0;i<S;i++)   // precompute the hash value of haystack substring from 0 till ith index 
        {
            hash[i+1]=(hash[i]+((h[i]-'a'+1)*power[i])%m)%m;
        }
        for(int i=0;i+P-1<S;i++)  
        {
            long long int cur_h=(hash[i+P]-hash[i]+m)%m;   // hash value of the window whose length is equal to the length of the needle string 
            if(cur_h==(hash_n*power[i])%m)  // basic concept of Hashing => value matches with a substing in haystack => return the index
            {
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;  //needle is not found 
    }
};
```
