# Approach
Two Pointer Approach.
Take 2 pointers Left and Right, left poining to start of the string(index 0) and Right poining to the length of needle (needle.length) :

1. If the length of needle and haystack is same (they are either the same string or not)
    1.(a) If they are same string, return 0;
    1.(b) Else, return -1 
2. If length of needle is greater than haystack, then you definitely won't find the needle in haysack. Hence return -1
3. Iterate the loop till the Right reaches the end of the the haystack. Create a substring of Haystack from Left to Right and compare it with needle, 
    3.(a) If both are same return Left index 
    3.(b) Else Increment Left and Right both by 1

If at the end of the loop, you still haven't found the needle in the Haystack, return -1  
